### Create a route

```
Example Request
```

```shell
curl "https://api.example.org/v3/routes" \
  -X POST \
  -H "Authorization: bearer [token]" \
  -H "Content-type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "host": "a-hostname",
    "relationships": {
      "domain": {
        "data": { "guid": "domain-guid" }
      },
      "space": {
        "data": { "guid": "space-guid" }
      }
    }
  }'
```

```
Example Response
```

```http
HTTP/1.1 201 Created
Content-Type: application/json

<%= yield_content :single_route %>
```

#### Definition
`POST /v3/routes`

#### Required Parameters

Name         | Type     | Description
------------ | -------  | -----------
| **space**  | [_to-one relationship_](#to-one-relationships) | A relationship to the space containing the route. Routes can only be mapped to destinations in that space. |
| **domain** | [_to-one relationship_](#to-one-relationships) | A relationship to the domain of the route.                                                                 |

#### Optional Parameters

Name         | Type     | Description
------------ | -------  | -----------
| host       | _string_ | The host component for the route. |

#### Permitted Roles

Role  | Notes
----- | ---
Admin |
Space Developer |

